---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalPage from '~/components/LegalPage.astro';
import { SITE } from '~/data/site';

const lang = 'en' as const;
---

<BaseLayout
  lang={lang}
  title="Cookie policy | Lifetime Weddings"
  description="Which cookies we use on lifetime.photo and how to manage them."
  canonicalPath="/cookies"
>
  <LegalPage lang={lang} title="Cookie policy">
    <p>A cookie is a small file downloaded to your device when you visit a website. Cookies allow the site to remember information about your visit.</p>

    <h2>Cookies we use</h2>

    <h3>Essential / technical</h3>
    <p>Required for the basic operation of the site. They do not require consent.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>lifetime.cookies.v1</strong> — remembers your choice on the cookie banner. Local storage (localStorage), no expiry.</li>
      <li><strong>Admin session</strong> — internal session cookie for the admin area. Deleted when you close the browser.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Analytics (require consent)</h3>
    <p>Allow us to analyse site usage anonymously to improve it. Only loaded if you accept cookies via the banner.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> (Google LLC, USA) — cookies <code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_HHBKJ291SF</code>. Identify unique visits and sessions. Duration: up to 2 years. IP anonymised. <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener">More info</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Social / embedded</h3>
    <p>Some content (YouTube, Instagram) may install third-party cookies when you interact with it.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>YouTube</strong> (Google LLC) — video playback cookies. Only loaded when you activate an embedded video.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
    <p>You can accept, reject or customise cookie use via the banner shown the first time you visit the site, and delete cookies at any time from your browser settings.</p>

    <h2>More information</h2>
    <p>For more information about data processing arising from cookies, see our <a href="/en/privacidad">privacy policy</a>, or write to <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.</p>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
